data.text:
No Debes Jugar (You Shouldn't Play Around)

No Debes Jugar was released as the lead single from Selena Live! album. It peaked at number 3 on the US Hot Latin Tracks on the week of ending August 14 1993

The song describes a woman whose life is centered on being unappreciated by her boyfriend. Then she finally stand up for herself and announcing she's done playing around and decides to leave.

No Debes Jugar received a "Song of the Year" nomination for the 1994 Tejano Music Awards.

The song wroted by Selena Y Los Dinos keyboardist Ricky Vela and Selena's brother AB Quintanilla III. The song intended to be the one of three studio tracks for Selena Live! album.

No Debes Jugar was recorded in Corpus Christi, Texas at Selena's father/manager Abraham Quintanilla's recording studio, Q Productions.

The theme of this song was about the women suggest empowerment.
